Banks Hill.label: Banks Hill
Banks Hill.description: Banks Hill was a French Thoroughbred Champion racehorse. She was bred and raced by Khalid Abdullah's Juddmonte Farms. Wikipedia

Biscay (horse).label: Biscay
Biscay (horse).description: Biscay was a brilliant two-year-old Thoroughbred racehorse that was bred in Australia in 1965 and who easily won the Maribyrnong Plate by eight lengths. Wikipedia

Dancethruthedawn.label: Dancethruthedawn
Dancethruthedawn.description: Dancethruthedawn is a Canadian Thoroughbred racehorse sired by leading United States stallion Mr. Prospector from Dance Smartly, a Canadian Triple Crown Champion mare and inductee of the Canadian and U.S. Racing Hall of Fame. Wikipedia

Bustino.label: Bustino
Bustino.description: Bustino was a British Thoroughbred Champion racehorse and sire. In a career which lasted from August 1973 until July 1975 he ran nine times and won five races. Wikipedia

Donau (horse).label: Donau
Donau (horse).description: Donau was an American Thoroughbred racehorse and was the winner of the 1910 Kentucky Derby. Donau was known for his often temperamental and difficult personality, which led to him being gelded at the end of 1910. Wikipedia

Charismatic (horse).label: Charismatic
Charismatic (horse).description: Charismatic is a stallion Thoroughbred horse, and is known as one of the closest challengers to the Triple Crown of Thoroughbred Racing since the last winner, Affirmed, accomplished the feat in 1978. Wikipedia
Awards: National Thoroughbred Racing Association Moment of the YearMore

Dream Ahead.label: Dream Ahead
Dream Ahead.description: Dream Ahead is a retired thoroughbred racehorse, who was bred in Kentucky and based in England during a nine race career which lasted from July 2010 to October 2011. Wikipedia

Flying Ebony.label: Flying Ebony
Flying Ebony.description: Flying Ebony was an American thoroughbred racehorse. He was bred by John E. Madden, who had already bred four Kentucky Derby winners, and was raced by New York carpet manufacturer, Gifford A. Cochran. Wikipedia

Grand Lodge (horse).label: Grand Lodge
Grand Lodge (horse).description: Grand Lodge was an American-bred, British-trained Thoroughbred racehorse. He was officially rated the best European two-year-old 1993. He won two Group One races; the Dewhurst Stakes in 1993 and the St. James's Palace Stakes in 1994. Wikipedia

Gustavus (horse).label: Gustavus
Gustavus (horse).description: Gustavus was a Thoroughbred racehorse that won the 1821 Epsom Derby. Gustavus was the first grey horse to win the Epsom Derby. He raced until he was four years old and was retired to stud in 1823. Wikipedia

King's Bishop.label: King's Bishop Stakes
King's Bishop.description: The King's Bishop Stakes is a Thoroughbred horse race run annually at the Saratoga Race Course in Saratoga Springs, New York. The race is open to three-year-olds willing to sprint seven furlongs on dirt. Wikipedia

Lady's Secret.label: Lady's Secret
Lady's Secret.description: Lady's Secret was an American Eclipse Award winning Thoroughbred racemare that was listed in the Top 100 U.S. Racehorses of the 20th Century. Wikipedia

Nonoalco.label: Nonoalco
Nonoalco.description: Nonoalco was an American-bred Thoroughbred racehorse who raced in France. He was out of the mare Seximee, a daughter of the 1954 Preakness Stakes winner Hasty Road. Wikipedia

Omar Khayyam (horse).label: Omar Khayyam
Omar Khayyam (horse).description: Omar Khayyam was a British-born Thoroughbred racehorse who was sold as a yearling to an American racing partnership and who became the first foreign-bred horse to win the Kentucky Derby. Wikipedia

Raja Baba.label: Raja Baba
Raja Baba.description: Raja Baba was an American Thoroughbred racehorse who became the 1980 Champion sire in North America. His sire was Bold Ruler, the leading sire in North America eight times and a National Museum of Racing and Hall of Fame inductee. Wikipedia

Ruffian (horse).label: Ruffian
Ruffian (horse).description: Ruffian was an American champion thoroughbred racehorse. Ruffian was ranked among the top U.S. racehorses of the 20th century by The Blood-Horse magazine. Her story was told in 2007 film Ruffian. Wikipedia

Sightseek.label: Sightseek
Sightseek.description: Sightseek is a retired American Thoroughbred racehorse and current broodmare. She was bred and raced by Khalid Abdullah's Juddmonte Farms and was trained by Bobby Frankel. Wikipedia

Sir Tatton Sykes.label: Sir Tatton Sykes
Sir Tatton Sykes.description: Sir Tatton Sykes, who also raced under the name Tibthorpe, was a British Thoroughbred racehorse and sire. In a career that lasted from spring 1846 to summer 1848 he ran eleven times and won four races. Wikipedia

St. Paddy.label: Saint Patrick's Day
St. Paddy.description: Saint Patrick's Day, or the Feast of Saint Patrick, is a cultural and religious holiday celebrated annually on 17 March, the death date of the most commonly-recognised patron saint of Ireland, Saint Patrick. Wikipedia

Sun Chariot (horse).label: Sun Chariot
Sun Chariot (horse).description:
Sun Chariot was a good Thoroughbred racehorse that won the Fillies Triple Crown series of races.
She was bred by the National Stud and raced for King George VI. Sun Chariot was a filly of great talent but very difficult temperament. Wikipedia

Tank's Prospect.label: Tank's Prospect
Tank's Prospect.description: Tank's Prospect was an American Thoroughbred racehorse best known for winning the second leg of the U.S. Triple Crown series, the Preakness Stakes. Wikipedia

The French Furze.label: The French Furze
The French Furze.description: The French Furze is an Irish Thoroughbred racehorse, born to sire, Be My Guest and dam, Exciting. He is owned by Jim Ennis and was trained by Nicky Richards. Wikipedia

Tulloch (horse).label: Tulloch
Tulloch (horse).description: Tulloch was a Thoroughbred racehorse, who is regarded as one of the three finest racehorses in Australian racing history. Wikipedia

War Admiral.label: War Admiral
War Admiral.description:
War Admiral was an American thoroughbred racehorse, the offspring of Man o' War and Brushup.
War Admiral was born at Faraway Farm in Lexington, Kentucky, and was owned by Samuel D. Riddle. Wikipedia

Blue Swords (horse).label: Blue Swords
Blue Swords (horse).description: Blue Swords was an American Thoroughbred race horse who debuted as a two-year-old in 1942. Bred in Kentucky by Samuel D. Riddle, he was owned by Allen T. Simmons of Akron, Ohio, a rubber mogul and radio station operator. Wikipedia

Bushranger (horse).label: Bushranger
Bushranger (horse).description: Bushranger was an American Thoroughbred steeplechase racehorse. Prepared for flat racing, at age two the grandson of Man o' War demonstrated little ability in that venue and as such his owner decided to try him in steeplechase racing. Wikipedia

Champs Elysees (horse).label: Champs Elysees
Champs Elysees (horse).description: Champs Elysees is a retired Thoroughbred racehorse who has competed successfully in Europe and North America. Wikipedia

Dauber (horse).label: Dauber
Dauber (horse).description: Dauber was an American Thoroughbred racehorse best known for winning the 1938 Preakness Stakes. Bred by Sonny Whitney, he was sired by Harry Payne Whitney's 1913 Futurity Stakes winner, Pennant. His dam was Ship of War, a daughter of Man o' War. Wikipedia

Enstone Spark.label: Enstone Spark
Enstone Spark.description: Enstone Spark is a Thoroughbred racehorse best known for winning the classic 1000 Guineas in 1978. Wikipedia

Fabius (horse).label: Fabius
Fabius (horse).description: Fabius was an American Thoroughbred racehorse. In a career that lasted from 1955 through 1957 he ran sixty-two times and won eighteen races. Wikipedia

Fastnet Rock (horse).label: Fastnet Rock
Fastnet Rock (horse).description:
Fastnet Rock is an Australian Thoroughbred racehorse stallion.
Sired by Danehill to dam Piccadilly Circus, he started his racing career in 2004. Wikipedia

Flagship Uberalles.label: Flagship Uberalles
Flagship Uberalles.description: Flagship Uberalles was a racehorse, a half brother to the 1994 and 1995 Queen Mother Champion Chase winner Viking Flagship, who raced between 1997 and 2005. Wikipedia

Indian Queen.label: Indian Queens
Indian Queen.description: Indian Queens is a village in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. The village is situated west of Goss Moor and north of Fraddon approximately ten miles west-southwest of Bodmin. Wikipedia

Katchit.label: Katchit
Katchit.description: Katchit was an Irish-bred, British-trained Thoroughbred racehorse, the peak of whose flat racing and hurdling career came in 2008 when, against the odds, he won the Champion Hurdle at the Cheltenham Festival. Wikipedia

Michelozzo (horse).label: Michelozzo
Michelozzo (horse).description: Michelozzo is a retired British Thoroughbred racehorse best known for winning the 1989 Classic St. Leger Stakes under jockey Steve Cauthen. Raced by Charles A. B. St-George, who had owned the great Ardross, Michelozzo was trained by Henry Cecil. Wikipedia

Night Nurse (horse).label: Night Nurse
Night Nurse (horse).description:
Night Nurse was an Irish bred English trained National Hunt racehorse sired by Falcon.
Timeform rated Night Nurse at 182, the highest rating ever awarded to a hurdler.
Night Nurse garnered 35 wins, winning a total of £174,507 viz. Wikipedia

One Cool Cat.label: One Cool Cat
One Cool Cat.description: One Cool Cat, foaled on March 26, 2001 in Kentucky, is a Thoroughbred racehorse who competed in England and Ireland. Wikipedia

Personal Ensign.label: Personal Ensign
Personal Ensign.description:
Personal Ensign was an American champion Thoroughbred racehorse.
A bay filly by Private Account out of Grecian Banner, she was the undefeated winner of 13 races and won $1,679,880 in the United States from 1986 to 1988. Wikipedia

Plucky Liege.label: Plucky Liege
Plucky Liege.description: Plucky Liege was a British Thoroughbred racemare who produced eleven winners, including an Epsom Derby winner at the age of twenty-three and three British Classic race winners. Wikipedia

Polynesian (horse).label: Polynesian
Polynesian (horse).description: Polynesian was an American Thoroughbred racehorse and sire. Wikipedia

Private Terms.label: Private Terms
Private Terms.description: Private Terms was a millionaire American Thoroughbred racehorse and successful stallion. He was the son of Private Account, who in turn was the son of the great Damascus. Wikipedia

Rockhill Native.label: Rockhill Native
Rockhill Native.description: Rockhill Native was an American Thoroughbred racehorse that was the 1979 American champion two-year-old colt. Wikipedia

Sinister Minister (horse).label: Sinister Minister
Sinister Minister (horse).description: Sinister Minister is a thoroughbred race horse. As a foal born on March 29, 2003, he was a possible contender for the Triple Crown in 2006. Wikipedia

Sunshine Forever.label: Sunshine Forever
Sunshine Forever.description: Sunshine Forever was an American Champion Thoroughbred racehorse. Bred by Darby Dan Farm owner John W. Galbreath who owned his dam, Outward Sunshine, and his damsire, Graustark, Sunshine Forever was ... Wikipedia

Sweep (horse).label: Sweep
Sweep (horse).description: Sweep was an American Thoroughbred racehorse. Wikipedia

Tejano Run.label: Tejano Run
Tejano Run.description: Tejano Run is an American Thoroughbred racehorse. Wikipedia

Wando (horse).label: Wando
Wando (horse).description: Wando is a Thoroughbred racehorse who won the Canadian Triple Crown in 2003. The chestnut stallion, raced with moderate success as a four-year-old then was retired on the 12th of May 2005 to stand at stud at Lane's End Farm near Lexington, Kentucky. Wikipedia

Agnes Tachyon.label: Agnes Tachyon
Agnes Tachyon.description:
Agnes Tachyon was an undefeated Japanese Thoroughbred racehorse and a Leading sire in Japan.
He was by Sunday Silence, his dam, Agnes Flora won the Oka Sho and his granddam Agnes Lady won the Yushun Himba. Wikipedia

Amberleigh House.label: Amberleigh House
Amberleigh House.description: Amberleigh House was the horse that won the 2004 Grand National. He is now retired and living at the National Stud in Newmarket. Wikipedia

Diesis (horse).label: Diesis
Diesis (horse).description: Diesis was a British Thoroughbred racehorse and sire. An outstanding two-year-old in 1982, he failed to live up to expectations at three, but went on to become an extremely successful breeding stallion, based in the United States. Wikipedia

Evening Attire (horse).label: Evening Attire
Evening Attire (horse).description: Evening Attire is a Kentucky-bred Thoroughbred racehorse, foaled on February 14, 1998, though most of his racing career took place in New York. Wikipedia

Falsetto (horse).label: Falsetto
Falsetto (horse).description: Falsetto was an American Thoroughbred Champion racehorse and outstanding sire. Bred and raced by J. W. Hunt Reynolds of Lexington, Kentucky, his dam was Farfaletta and his sire was General Abe Buford's very good runner, Enquirer. Wikipedia

Mumtaz Mahal (horse).label: Mumtaz Mahal
Mumtaz Mahal (horse).description: Mumtaz Mahal was a British Thoroughbred racehorse who the National Sporting Library's Thoroughbred Heritage website says was "one of the most important broodmares of the 20th Century". Wikipedia

Cherokee Run.label: Cherokee Run Golf Course- Maintainance Building

Daiwa Scarlet.label: Daiwa Scarlet
Daiwa Scarlet.description: Daiwa Scarlet is a Japanese racehorse which won the 2007 Oka Sho, Shūka Sho, Queen Elizabeth II Commemorative Cup and the 2008 Arima Kinen. Wikipedia

El Condor Pasa (horse).label: El Condor Pasa
El Condor Pasa (horse).description: El Condor Pasa was an American-bred, Japanese-trained Thoroughbred racehorse. In 1998 he won the NHK Mile Cup and the Japan Cup. Wikipedia

Henrythenavigator.label: Henrythenavigator
Henrythenavigator.description: Henrythenavigator is an American-bred and Irish-trained Thoroughbred racehorse. He won the 2,000 Guineas, the Irish 2,000 Guineas, the St. James's Palace Stakes and the Sussex Stakes in 2008. Wikipedia

Inglis Drever.label: Inglis Drever
Inglis Drever.description: Inglis Drever was a champion racehorse trained in the North of England by Howard Johnson. He was one of the most successful hurdle racing horses to date and won the World Hurdle three times, matched only by the former champion Big Buck's. Wikipedia

Nijinsky's Secret.label: Nijinsky's Secret
Nijinsky's Secret.description: Nijinsky's Secret is a Thoroughbred racehorse who competed in France, Canada, and the United States. Wikipedia

Noblesse (horse).label: Noblesse
Noblesse (horse).description: Noblesse was a champion thoroughbred racehorse and has been regarded as the greatest filly ever trained in Ireland. Wikipedia

Raven's Pass.label: Raven's Pass
Raven's Pass.description: Raven's Pass is an American-bred, British-trained Thoroughbred racehorse most notable for being the first English-trained winner of the Grade I Breeders' Cup Classic at Santa Anita Park in Arcadia, California. Wikipedia

Roman Brother.label: Roman Brother
Roman Brother.description: Roman Brother was an American Champion Thoroughbred racehorse. As a two-year-old, Roman Brother was initially overshadowed by his stable companion Raise a Native before emerging as one of the year's ... Wikipedia

Silence Suzuka.label: Silence Suzuka
Silence Suzuka.description: Silence Suzuka was a Japanese Thoroughbred racehorse who won the Grade I Takarazuka Kinen in 1998. Wikipedia

Taiki Shuttle.label: Taiki Shuttle
Taiki Shuttle.description: Taiki Shuttle is an American-bred, Japanese-trained Thoroughbred race horse. Wikipedia

Rooster Booster (horse).label: Rooster Booster
Rooster Booster (horse).description: Rooster Booster was a British-bred thoroughbred racehorse, best known for winning the 2003 Champion Hurdle. Wikipedia

Thor's Echo.label: Thor's Echo
Thor's Echo.description:
Thor's Echo is an American Champion Thoroughbred racehorse best known for becoming only the second California-bred horse to ever win a Breeders' Cup race.
Thor's Echo began racing at age two and in 2005 as a three-year-old he won the WinStar Derby. Wikipedia

Triple Bend.label: Triple Bend
Triple Bend.description: Triple Bend was an American Thoroughbred racehorse who set a world record time of 119.80 for seven furlongs on dirt in winning the 1972 Los Angeles Handicap. Wikipedia

Venetian Way.label: Venetian Way
Venetian Way.description: Venetian Way was an American Thoroughbred racehorse best known for winning the 1960 Kentucky Derby. Bred in Kentucky by John W. Greathouse, he was purchased by Chicago, Illinois businessman Isaac Blumberg ... Wikipedia

San San (horse).label: San San
San San (horse).description: San San was an American-bred Thoroughbred Champion racehorse in France. Bred by Harry F. Guggenheim, the granddaughter of Nasrullah was bought by Countess Margit Batthyany, owner of Haras du Bois-Roussel at Alençon, Orne, in France. Wikipedia
